<br>
Maybe high end raid level caster mobs we're easy targets, but while &quot;fixing&quot; the high end, they ruined everything else. Caster mobs are very challanging to most players. They chain nuke you to death with channeling that rivals the gods. Mezzed healers still heal their friends, wizards need no time to pause to cast a spell (players have to stop for a second or 2 to ensure the game knows they stopped), and ALL casters hit just as hard as non casters, so they can run quad you for 150 then grav flux your whole party with out skipping a beat.<br>
<br>
I can except some increased spell selection like root, malase, and tash. I can except some new AI for these mobs where they debuff you then root you then nuke you. But mobs that are already well tuned melee having access to <br>
spells above thier level is unfair and VERY unbalancing.<br>
<br>
Remember a alittle while back the push Verant had for more people to enter dungeons? Giving some more XP bonuses,  additional spells? Guess what, aside from the very high end game(because you have to), they just drove alot of people back out of the dungeons. Casting mobs that you have no chance of out running and now cast better spells then your own teammates will make for lots of CRs and more bad press for dungeons.<br>
